  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A structured consent process, in combination with one or a number of the aforementioned
      modalities (nursing education, handout, video, etc), may reasonably be expected to improve
      surgical informed consent. The investigators hypothesized that overall patient
      knowledge/retention would be influenced by the type of consent process and that more
      intensive training and review would result in better patient retention and recall. The
      investigators further hypothesized that the knowledge retention would decline following the
      consent process and surgery, but in a stratified manner based on the nature of preoperative
      teaching.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
